author: 13abc
title: Toledo Police respond to cyclist hit
text:
TOLEDO, Ohio (13abc Action News) - Toledo Police responded to a bicyclist hit at the intersection of Arlington and Byrne Monday afternoon.
According to police, the bicyclist was crossing the street when a car driving southbound on Byrne hit him.
He was taken to a local hospital with a suspected broken ankle, and is expected to be okay.
Police are still deciding who is at fault.
Traffic in the area was backed up during rush hour.
